{
  "text": "Another application of Lemma 4.1 is the following. There exist strongly regular graphs with parameters (35, 18, 9, 9) for the 2-ranks 6, 8, 10, 12 and 14; see [CITATION_1] . Let H * be the associated normalized graphical Hadamard matrix of order 36, and let H be as before, then H \u2297 H * is associated with a strongly regular graph with parameters (143, 72, 36, 36). By Lemma 4.1 we find that such strongly regular graphs exist for every even 2-rank between 8 and 16.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "26511445"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "26511445": {
      "title": "Binary codes of strongly regular graphs",
      "abstract": "For strongly regular graphs ith adjacency matrix A, we look at the binary codes generated by A and A+I. We determine these codes for some families of graphs, e pay attention to the relation beteen the codes of switching equivalent graphs and, ith the exception of two parameter sets, we generate by computer the codes of all knon strongly regular graphs on fewer than 45 vertices."
    }
